@startuml FaithfulChain — Auditor Scoring Logic

!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam defaultFontName Inter
skinparam defaultFontSize 13
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam RoundCorner 10
skinparam Padding 8
skinparam linetype ortho

skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #EEEDFE
  BorderColor #534AB7
  FontColor #26215C
  FontSize 13
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FAEEDA
  DiamondBorderColor #854F0B
  DiamondFontColor #412402
}

skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #F1EFE8
  BorderColor #5F5E5A
  FontColor #2C2C2A
  FontSize 11
}

title FaithfulChain — Auditor Scoring and Flagging Logic

|Reasoner|
start
:Generate reasoning step
with atomic claim and citations;

|Auditor|
:Receive step JSON from Reasoner;

fork
  :Score **Logical Validity**;
  note right
    Does the conclusion follow
    from the stated premises?
    Threshold ≥ **0.75**
  end note
fork again
  :Score **Reference Integrity**;
  note right
    Does it correctly use
    the steps it cites?
    Threshold ≥ **0.80**
  end note
fork again
  :Score **Necessity Score**;
  note right
    Would removing this step
    break the final answer?
    Threshold ≥ **0.65**
  end note
end fork

:Compute composite score
(OR logic — strictest check);

note right
  **Flagged = true** if
  ANY one dimension
  falls below its threshold
end note

if (Any dimension\nbelow threshold?) then (yes — flagged)

  :Attach explanation text
  describing the weakness;

  |Human Reviewer|
  :View step + scores
  in VerdictPanel;

  if (Human verdict?) then (Agree)
    :Auditor was correct —
    log diverged = **false**;
  else if (verdict?) then (Disagree)
    :Auditor was wrong —
    log diverged = **true**\n← research signal;
  else (Unsure)
    :Log diverged = **null**
    (valid research data);
  endif

  |Storage|
  :Append full record
  to divergence_log.jsonl;

else (no — passes)

  |Frontend|
  :Show step with
  green border in ChainPanel;

  note right
    No human action required
    for passing steps
  end note
endif

|Aggregator|
:Compute session stats:
divergence rate, worst dimension;

stop

@enduml
